        "comment": "In some localities up to 10 cm of snow will fall. <br/> <br/> West, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2200 m: <br/> Wind slabs are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. <br/> Avalanche prone weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack. <br/> <br/> Steep sunny slopes: Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise to moistening of the snowpack. In the event of solar radiation this applies in particular."
      },
